at%20the%20numbers%20show%20is%20a%20two-tier%20job%20market%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0one%20divided%20between%20a%20blue-collar%20boom%20and%20a%20white-collar%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20Vanguard's%20lowest%20earners%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20make%20less%20than%20%2455%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20the%20hiring%20rate%20has%20held%20up%20well.%20At%201.5%25%2C%20it's%20still%20above%20pre-pandemic%20levels.%20But%20among%20those%20who%20make%20more%20than%20%2496%2C000%3F%20It's%20pretty%20depressing.%20Hiring%20has%20slowed%20to%20a%20dismal%200.5%25%2C%20less%20than%20half%20the%20peak%20it%20reached%20in%20mid-2022.%20Excluding%20the%20dip%20in%20the%20early%20months%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20that's%20the%20worst%20it's%20been%20since%202014.%20If%20you%20make%20a%20six-figure%20salary%2C%20it%20really%20is%20a%20bad%20time%20to%20be%20looking%20for%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FzD0cC%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Hiring%20rate%20by%20wage%20bracket%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22465%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20here%20is%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Why%20are%20companies%20hiring%20so%20few%20white-collar%20workers%20right%20now%3F%20Several%20possible%20explanations%20come%20to%20mind.%20It%20might%20be%20that%20fewer%20people%20in%20corporate%20jobs%20are%20quitting%20right%20now%2C%20which%20would%20mean%20companies%20have%20fewer%20openings%20they%20need%20to%20fill.%20It%20might%20be%20that%20the%20industries%20that%20are%20struggling%20the%20most%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0tech%20and%20finance%20%E2%80%94%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20employ%20a%20lot%20of%20high-earning%20professionals.%20Or%20it%20might%20be%20that%20CEOs%20are%20making%20good%20on%20their%20threats%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20what%20they%20see%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-great-flattening-organization-meta-tech-layoffs-firing-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorporate%20bloat%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0what%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20has%20called%20%26quot%3Bmanagers%20managing%20managers%2C%20managing%20managers%2C%20managing%20managers%2C%20managing%20the%20people%20who%20are%20doing%20the%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20could%20be%20a%20bigger%2C%20more%20worrisome%20explanation%20for%20the%20downturn%20in%20white-collar%20hiring.%20Maybe%20companies%20are%20anticipating%20tough%20times%20ahead%20and%20trimming%20their%20budgets%20accordingly.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20need%20to%20pull%20back%20on%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Fiona%20Greig%2C%20the%20global%20head%20of%20investor%20research%20and%20policy%20at%20Vanguard%2C%20%26quot%3Bpulling%20back%20on%20expensive%20workers%20will%20reduce%20costs%20to%20a%20greater%20extent%20than%20pulling%20back%20on%20your%20lower-income%20workers.%26quot%3B%20Translation%3A%20The%20more%20you%20earn%20when%20budgets%20are%20tight%2C%20the%20less%20an%20employer%20wants%20to%20hire%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20you%20could%20argue%20that%20a%20slowdown%20in%20white-collar%20hiring%20doesn't%20really%20matter%20in%20the%20current%20economy%2C%20even%20for%20white-collar%20workers.%20Sure%2C%20Vanguard's%20data%20show%20that%20things%20are%20tough%20for%20professionals%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20job.%20But%20there%20aren't%20that%20many%20people%20who%20actually%20%3Cem%3Eneed%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20new%20job%20right%20now%3A%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20people%20with%20a%20college%20degree%20is%202.1%25%2C%20and%20the%20national%20layoff%20rate%20is%20below%20what%20it%20was%20pre-pandemic.%20When%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20professionals%20already%20have%20a%20job%20%E2%80%94%20and%20are%20able%20to%20keep%20their%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20it's%20OK%20that%20companies%20aren't%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20argument%20doesn't%20take%20into%20account%20one%20important%20factor%3A%20What%20if%20the%20job%20you%20have%20is%20one%20you%20hate%3F%20I%20have%20several%20friends%20who%20are%20unhappy%20in%20their%20current%20jobs%2C%20but%20they%20can't%20quit%20because%20no%20one%20is%20hiring.%20Some%20observers%20have%20called%20this%20combination%20of%20lower%20hiring%20and%20less%20quitting%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Big%20Stay%2C%26quot%3B%20suggesting%20a%20kind%20of%20equilibrium%20after%20the%20chaos%20of%20the%20Great%20Resignation.%20But%20my%20colleague%20Emily%20Stewart%20has%20a%20better%20name%20for%20it%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-housing-market-mortgage-buying-car-interest-rates-new-jobs-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Btrapped%20in%20place%26quot%3B%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20think%20professionals%20feel%20this%20trapped-in-placeness%20particularly%20acutely.%20After%20all%2C%20it%20wasn't%20that%20long%20ago%20that%20they%20were%20enjoying%20a%20%26quot%3Btake%20this%20job%20and%20shove%20it%26quot%3B%20swagger%2C%20which%20was%20fun%20to%20watch.%20During%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-great-reshuffle-upward-mobility-quitting-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Great%20Resignation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20knew%20it'd%20be%20easy%20to%20find%20a%20new%20job%2C%20which%20meant%20it'd%20be%20easy%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20their%20current%20one.%20Even%20if%20they%20weren't%20planning%20to%20leave%2C%20the%20job%20market%20gave%20them%20a%20sense%20of%20freedom%20%E2%80%94%20the%20feeling%20that%20they%20no%20longer%20had%20to%20put%20up%20with%20a%20bad%20boss%2C%20or%20a%20brutal%20workload%2C%20or%20an%20arbitrary%20return-to-office%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20what%20explains%20what%20people%20are%20calling%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibecession-recession-hiring-outlook-american-economic-sentiment-rising-prices-recovery-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evibecession%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3A%20the%20weird%20state%20of%20%3Cem%3Efeeling%3C%2Fem%3E%20like%20we're%20in%20a%20recession%20even%20though%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-pce-inflation-recovery-vibecession-consumer-spending-soft-landing-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estandard%20metrics%20show%20we're%20not%3C%2Fa%3E.%20What%20we're%20experiencing%20is%20actually%20a%20slowdown%20in%20%3Cem%3Ewhite-collar%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehiring%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20white-collar%20professionals%20(me%20and%20my%20angsty%20friends)%20are%20the%20people%20who%20shape%20the%20public%20discourse%20about%20the%20economy.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20feel%20that%20things%20are%20moving%20in%20the%20wrong%20direction%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Guy%20Berger%2C%20the%20director%20of%20economic%20research%20at%20the%20Burning%20Glass%20Institute%2C%20which%20analyzes%20the%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20the%20most%20elite%20professionals%2C%20things%20could%20get%20worse%20before%20they%20get%20better.%20Berger%20tells%20me%20he%20doesn't%20expect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2024-outlook-us-economy-stock-market-jobs-inflation-interest-rates-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20full-on%20recession%20anytime%20soon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20he's%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20people%20with%20advanced%20degrees.%20Pretty%20much%20everyone%20else%20is%20doing%20OK%2C%20job-wise%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20there's%20been%20a%20slight%20uptick%20for%20all%20the%20smarty-pants%20with%20master's%20degrees%20and%20doctorates.%20They%20aren't%20exactly%20struggling%20right%20now.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20still%20talking%20about%20the%20people%20that%20have%20the%20highest%20pay%20in%20the%20job%20market%20and%20the%20lowest%20unemployment%20rate%2C%26quot%3B%20Berger%20says.%20But%20for%20them%2C%20hiring%20is%20headed%20in%20the%20wrong%20direction.%20And%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-productivity-boost-job-performance-inequality-economics-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20tools%20increasingly%20encroach%20on%20professionals'%20tasks%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0writing%2C%20coding%2C%20coordination%2C%20analysis%20%E2%80%94%20we'll%20likely%20see%20a%20lot%20more%20weakness%20at%20the%20higher%20end%20of%20the%20income%20scale%20than%20at%20the%20lower%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20story%20we're%20used%20to%20hearing%20about%20employment.%20For%20decades%20the%20economy%20has%20been%20leaving%20workers%20with%20lower%20incomes%20and%20less%20education%20behind%20while%20professionals%20have%20reaped%20all%20the%20gains.%20But%20now%20those%20roles%20are%20reversed%2C%20and%20it's%20the%20high%20earners%20who%20are%20taking%20the%20hit.%20No%20wonder%20everyone%20is%20confused%20about%20how%20the%20economy%20is%20doing.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20having%20some%20trouble%20collectively%20digesting%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Berger%20says.%20And%20the%20longer%20the%20white-collar%20hiring%20lull%20continues%2C%20he%20warns%2C%20the%20more%20the%20resentment%20will%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20there's%20no%20big%20surge%20in%20layoffs%2C%20people%20are%20just%20going%20to%20get%20grumpier%20and%20more%20dissatisfied%2C%26quot%3B%20Berger%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20continues%20for%20three%20or%20four%20more%20years%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20cause%20a%20lot%20of%20discontent%20and%20low%20morale%20in%20corporate%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20a