0Jones%20said%20some%20people%20still%20turn%20them%20into%20accusations%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BI%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Efeel%20like%20you're%20being%20disrespectful%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20your%20heart's%20not%20really%20in%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20added%20that%20it's%20natural%20to%20have%20images%20in%20our%20minds%20of%20other%20people's%20motivations%20and%20values%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bneed%20to%20be%20updated%26quot%3B%20for%20relationships%20to%20flourish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20They%20want%20agreement%2C%20not%20compromise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20said%20that%20often%2C%20cofounders%20start%20loving%20how%20complimentary%20their%20differences%20are.%20They%20see%20one%20person%20filling%20in%20gaps%20for%20the%20other%2C%20embracing%20their%20unique%20dynamic%20as%20a%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInevitably%2C%20these%20differences%20will%20come%20to%20a%20head%20under%20pressure.%20Instead%20of%20finding%20a%20way%20to%20meet%20in%20the%20middle%2C%20some%20people%20will%20just%20dub%20the%20relationship%20a%20bad%20fit%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20is%20faulty%20thinking%20for%20two%20reasons%3A%20Primarily%2C%20successful%20companies%20need%20diverse%20personalities%20to%20ensure%20a%20range%20of%20skill%20sets%20and%20perspectives%20are%20covered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20a%20perfect%20match%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20differences%20that%20need%20to%20be%20respected%20and%20managed%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20founder%20is%20more%20cautious%20while%20the%20other%20wants%20to%20move%20fast%20and%20break%20things%2C%20Jones%20will%20try%20to%20work%20with%20them%20to%20find%20the%20optimal%20outcomes%20for%20the%20company%2C%20which%20usually%20involves%20finding%20common%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20They%20ignore%20major%20differenc