ollow%20our%20instructions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELength%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20primary%20dimension%20used%20to%20determine%20the%20size%20of%20a%20raincoat%20is%20the%20length%20of%20a%20dog's%20back.%20Measure%20your%20dog%20from%20the%20top%20of%20their%20tail%20to%20their%20shoulder%20blades%20while%20they%20are%20standing%20in%20a%20relaxed%20position.%20If%20your%20measurement%20falls%20between%20sizes%2C%20size%20up.%20Some%20brands%20may%20recommend%20a%20specific%20size%20for%20certain%20breeds.%20This%20may%20be%20helpful%2C%20but%20don't%20follow%20their%20suggestions%20alone%2C%20as%20sizes%20can%20vary%20among%20a%20single%20breed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChest%20girth%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Dog%20raincoats%20are%20also%20commonly%20measured%20by%20chest%20girth.%20This%20is%20an%20important%20figure%20to%20get%20right%20because%20many%20jackets%20are%20not%20adjustable%20around%20the%20chest.%20That's%20doubly%20true%20if%20you%20have%20a%20broad-%20or%20barrel-chested%20pup.%20To%20get%20this%20figure%2C%20measure%20the%20circumference%20of%20your%20dog's%20chest%20while%20they%20are%20standing%20in%20a%20relaxed%20position%2C%20wrapping%20the%20tape%20right%20behind%20the%20legs%20at%20the%20chest's%20widest%20point.%20If%20your%20dog's%20chest%20girth%20falls%20between%20sizes%2C%20choose%20the%20larger%20option%2C%20especially%20if%20your%20dog%20does%20a%20lot%20of%20running%20and%20jumping.%20A%20highly%20active%20dog%20may%20benefit%20from%20a%20jacket%20that%20is%20an%20inch%20or%20two%20wider%20than%20their%20actual%20measurement%20because%20it%20will%20allow%20their%20front%20legs%20more%20freedom%20of%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeck%20girth%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETo%20make%20sure%20your%20jacket%20won't%20be%20too%20tight%20around%20the%20neck%2C%20measure%20around%20the%20thickest%20part%20right%20below%20the%20collar.%20This%20is%20particularly%20important%20if%20the%20coat's%20neck%20lacks%20an%20adjustable%20opening.%20When%20in%20doubt%2C%20size%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrop%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Occasionally%2C%20brands%20offer%20a%20drop%20measurement%20to%20help%20you%20get%20the%20right%20fit.%20The%20drop%20is%20how%20low%20a%20jacket%20hangs%20on%20a%20dog's%20body%20and%20legs.%20Too%20long%20and%20it%20may%20restrict%20movement%3B%20too%20short%2C%20and%20your%20pup%20may%20get%20wet%20by%20the%20end%20of%20a%20walk.%20Your%20dog's%20raincoat%20should%20extend%20at%20most%20halfway%20down%20the%20leg.%20To%20figure%20out%20how%20a%20jacket%20will%20lay%20on%20your%20dog%2C%20compare%20half%20its%20width%20to%20the%20distance%20between%20the%20top%20of%20your%20dog's%20tail%20to%20the%20ankle%20of%20their%20hind%20leg%20just%20above%20the%20paw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20do%20you%20walk%20your%20dog%20on%20a%20rainy%20day%3F%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20dog%20hates%20leaving%20the%20house%20when%20the%20rain%20starts%20to%20fall%2C%20these%20tips%20for%20wet-weather%20walking%20will%20make%20sure%20you%20get%20their%20most%20important%20daily%20needs%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20the%20right%20gear%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Make%20rainy%20day%20walks%20more%20enjoyable%20by%20getting%20your%20pup%20one%20of%20the%20best%20dog%20raincoats.%20A%20properly%20fitted%20coat%20that%20covers%20both%20the%20chest%20and%20belly%20will%20prevent%20your%20dog%20from%20splashing%20water%20against%20the%20most%20sensitive%20parts%20of%20their%20body.%20If%20your%20dog%20has%20sensitive%20paws%2C%20you%20may%20also%20want%20to%20consider%20getting%20a%20set%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-dog-boots%5C%22%3Ebest%20dog%20boots%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlan%20ahead%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Unless%20the%20forecast%20calls%20for%20extreme%20weather%2C%20most%20rainy%20days%20have%20at%20least%20a%20couple%20of%20periods%20in%20which%20showers%20slow%20to%20a%20sprinkle.%20Use%20a%20weather%20tracking%20app%20or%20website%20to%20help%20you%20predict%20when%20a%20storm%20will%20lighten%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEncourage%2C%20don't%20force%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Even%20if%20you%20have%20the%20proper%20rain%20gear%20for%20your%20pup%2C%20your%20dog%20may%20still%20avoid%20the%20rain%20at%20all%20costs.%20These%20dogs%20will%20likely%20require%20an%20extra%20incentive.%20Before%20getting%20ready%20to%20go%2C%20stuff%20your%20pockets%20full%20of%20treats%20and%20offer%20them%20before%20you%20step%20out%20the%20door.%20If%20putting%20on%20rain%20gear%20predicts%20that%20treats%20will%20follow%2C%20your%20dog%20will%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20allow%20you%20to%20get%20them%20dressed.%20Use%20your%20treats%20to%20entice%20your%20dog%20out%20the%20door%20instead%20of%20forcing%20them%20to%20go%20out%20into%20the%20rain%2C%20which%20will%20only%20make%20them%20more%20frightened%20and%20stressed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlay%20the%20%26quot%3BFind%20It%26quot%3B%20game%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Keep%20the%20treats%20flowing%20once%20outside.%20Try%20encouraging%20your%20dog%20to%20walk%20with%20the%20Find%20It%20game.%20Throw%20a%20treat%20a%20few%20feet%20in%20front%20of%20your%20dog%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3Bfind%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20happy%20tone.%20Let%20them%20gobble%20up%20the%20treat%2C%20then%20throw%20your%20next%20one%2C%20repeating%20the%20phrase.%20Play%20the%20game%20as%20much%20as%20necessary%20during%20the%20walk%20to%20get%20your%20pup's%20mind%20off%20the%20water%20falling%20from%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20expect%20a%20regular%20walk%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Even%20with%20plenty%20of%20treats%20and%20encouragement%2C%20dogs%20who%20really%20hate%20the%20rain%20aren't%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stay%20outdoors%20for%20long.%20If%20they%20go%20potty%20and%20then%20refuse%20to%20go%20any%20farther%2C%20that's%20OK.%20Bring%20them%20back%20inside%20and%20make%20up%20the%20missed%20exercise%20with%20play%20or%20indoor%20training.%20Re