0and%20East-flowing%20Manganga%20river%2C%20called%20%E2%80%98Manavganga%E2%80%99%20in%20Sanskrit%2C%20rises%20in%20the%20eastern%20hills%20of%20the%20Satara%20district%20and%20courses%20through%20five%20drought-prone%20talukas.%20These%20are%20namely%20Dahiwadi%20(Man)%2C%20Atpadi%2C%20Sangola%2C%20Mangalvedha%20and%20Pandharpur%2C%20before%20it%20finally%20joins%20the%20Bhima%20River%20at%20Sarkoli.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20drought-prone%20districts%2C%20falling%20under%20the%20rain%20shadow%20region%20of%20Sangli%2C%20Satara%20and%20Solapur%2C%20receive%20rainfall%20ranging%20between%20584mm%20and%20762%20mm.%20It%20occasionally%20experiences%20floods%20too%2C%20like%20it%20did%20back%20in%20August%202019%20and%20October%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20accumulated%20silt%20in%20Manganga%20had%20rendered%20it%20shallow%20and%20when%20the%20downpour%20was%20intense%2C%20the%20river%20was%20unable%20to%20carry%20the%20rainwater%20further%20downstream%2C%20causing%20floods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202057px)%20100vw%2C%202057px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222057%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ghongade%20overseeing%20the%20shrub%20removal%20work%20being%20done.%20Shrubs%20of%20morning%20glory%20had%20captured%20the%20river's%20banks%2C%20restricting%20water%20flow.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542.jpg%202057w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FAn-eathmover-removes-shrubs-of-morning-glory_11zon-1713963542-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2